{"title":"How to watch and livestream Il Lombardia 2023","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/il-lombardia-watch","date":1696522232000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/il-lombardia-watch\">How to watch and livestream Il Lombardia 2023</a></p>\n\n<p>The last Monument of the season, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/il-lombardia\" target=\"_blank\">Il Lombardia</a>, will take place on Saturday 7th October 2023. Dubbed ‘The Race of the Falling Leaves’ because it is held in autumn, the 238km route will this year depart from Como and taken on climbs such as the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/classic-climb-madonna-del-ghisallo\" target=\"_blank\">Madonna del Ghisallo</a>, Zambla Alta and Passo di Ganda towards Bergamo in Italy.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Defending champion <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tadej-pogacar\" target=\"_blank\">Tadej Pogačar</a> (UAE Team Emirates) will be on the start line and attempting a three-peat. He faces competition from rivals such as Remco Evenepoel (Soudal-QuickStep) and Primož Roglič (Jumbo-Visma).</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/il-lombardia-favourites\">Who are the favourites for Il Lombardia 2023?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/il-lombardia-history\">Remembering the first Il Lombardia in 1905</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/il-lombardia-preview\">Il Lombardia 2023: Everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>How to watch and live stream Il Lombardia 2023 </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"cyclist celebrating victory\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Pogacar-wins-Lombardia-2022-by-Tim-de-Waele.jpg 1654w\" /><figcaption>Tim de Waele/Getty Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Live coverage of Il Lombardia will be available on TV and streaming services such as GCN+, Eurosport and Discovery+.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://plus.globalcyclingnetwork.com/subscribe\" target=\"_blank\">GCN+</a> costs £6.99 paid monthly, or £39.99 per year and <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> costs £6.99 per month or £59.99 per year for sports <em>and </em>entertainment (for fans of shows like Wheeler Dealers<em> </em>and Naked and Afraid). The GCN+ broadcast of Il Lombardia is available worldwide including Australia, Canada, New Zealand and the United States, although best to check GCN’s <a href=\"https://help.globalcyclingnetwork.com/hc/en-gb/sections/360004434020-What-can-I-watch-\" target=\"_blank\">‘What can I watch?</a> page to double-check.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>TV viewers in the UK can also watch on the Eurosport 2 channel.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Il Lombardia 2023: Live TV guide</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Coverage time and channel subject to change.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>GCN+:</strong> 09:00-16:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 2:</strong> 10:15-16:30.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more on Il Lombardia, visit our <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/il-lombardia\" target=\"_blank\">hub page</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/il-lombardia-watch\">How to watch and livestream Il Lombardia 2023</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Robyn Davidson &#124; Editorial Assistant","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"46f6ff146bd72f283987a7d2ad4d9491944d145d85a1c6be79b3015ef63ee5fb","category":"Cycling"}